node.text:
Russian Doctor Alexander Volchek, an obstetrician-gynecologist from Novosibirsk, Russia, has recently made headlines in Russian by implanting several tiny chips in his hand and arm. The chips can perform several daily tasks like opening the doors at his place of work, paying for things with his credit card, and even storing his personal identification. This not only allows him to carry less cards, but also decreases his risk of identity theft. What do you guys think? Y'all getting one? 

Follow @yup.that.exists

node.text:
New York-based restaurant Serendipity 3 currently holds the Guiness World Record for most expensive sandwich with their "Quintessential Grilled Cheese". The mouth watering sandwich is priced at $214 and is made with two pieces of French Pullman champagne bread, prepared with Dom Perignon champagne and even some edible edible gold flakes! 

If anyone wants to buy this PB&J sandwich I just made off me for $215 we can brake the record? 

Follow @yup.that.exists

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Yup That Exists on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YUP Yup That Exists @yup.that.exists Tel Aviv, Isreal passes law to require DNA from dogs in order to track down owners who don't pick up after them.'.

node.text:
Tel Aviv, Israel has recently passed a law to try and hold responsibility to pet owners that don't pick up their feces. The new law lets municipal inspectors collect samples of dog feces left in the streets and use the DNA to find the animal’s owner and fine them. 

What do you guys think? Good idea or bad idea? 

Follow @yup.that.exists
